Title : Western House of Refuge
Text : The '''Western House of Refuge''' was a [[youth detention center]] in [[Rochester, New York|Rochester]], [[New York (state)|New York]]; it was the first state managed reformatory in the United States, housing males under the age of eighteen who had been convicted of [[felonies]] in courts located in the central and western part of New York State. In 1876, a Female Department was established; in 1886, the name was changed to the '''State Industrial School'''. In 1907, it was renamed the '''State Agricultural & Industrial School'''<ref>[http://www.archives.nysed.gov/a/research/res_topics_legal_corrections.pdf "Records of the New York State Agricultural and Industrial School" in: Andress, Richard. ''Guide to Records of the Department of Correctional Services'' Albany, New York: New York State Archives, Publication FA07 (1992)]</ref> and moved to [[Industry, New York]]. Its former drill hall was transformed into [[Edgerton Park Arena]].

It operated from 1849-1960.<ref>[http://www.archives.nysed.gov/a/research/res_topics_gen_guide_prison.shtml "Prison and Reformatory Records" New York State Archives website]</ref>

